 ('62', '62', 'en_us', 'Apply for a Disabled Parking \"Blue Zone\"', '', '', '', '<h3>Disabled Parking Zone “Blue Zone” Program</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A “blue zone” provides on-street parking for people with disabilities. The “blue zone” has a painted blue curb with a posted sign.</p><p>Residents and businesses can request “blue zones” from the Disabled Parking Zone program.<br>The City does not install “blue zones” for paratransit drop-off and pick-up.</p><h4>Download the application form to request a “blue zone.”</h4><p><br><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/form/oak051831.pdf\">Residential Blue Zone Application Form</a><br><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/form/oak051832.pdf\">Non-Residential Blue Zone Application Form</a></p><p><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/form/oak051832.pdf\"></a><br>To learn more, please read the Policy summaries below.</p><p><br><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/policy/oak051830.pdf\">Residential Blue Zone Policy Summary<br></a><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/pwa/documents/policy/oak051829.pdf\">Non-Residential Blue Zone Policy Summary</a></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 21:40:10', '2016-01-07 00:52:20', '0ef0babd-6f37-4f85-a36e-838481207a96'),
 ('72', '72', 'en_us', 'Apply for a Parking Obstruction Permit', '', '​Do you need to block parking spaces or traffic? If your portable storage unit or moving truck will block parking on a public street or right of way, you will need an Obstruction Permit.', '', '<p>An Obstruction Permit allows you to park the pod, portable storage unit or moving truck in one site for a limited amount of time.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"how-the-obstruction-permit-works\">How the Obstruction Permit Works</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>The Obstruction Permit tells nearby property owners that they can not park in the permitted site for a limited amount of time.</li>\r\n  <li>You may only block the street or right of way that you are moving from or to.</li>\r\n  <li>You need to post the NO PARKING sign(s) that you receive with the Obstruction Permit at least 72 hours (3 days) before parking the portable storage unit or moving truck.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"how-to-apply-for-an-obstruction-permit\">How to Apply for an Obstruction Permit</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You can only apply for an Obstruction Permit in person at the Permit Center. To avoid long line, visit the Permit Center early in the day before the busiest time from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>Please bring the following information.</li>\r\n  <li>Site address.</li>\r\n  <li>Dates required.</li>\r\n  <li>Number of parking spaces required. One parking space is 25 feet long.</li>\r\n  <li>Meter numbers if you are blocking parking meters</li>\r\n  <li>Contact phone number for the company or person applying.</li>\r\n  <li>If related to work requiring permit, please reference permit application number.</li>\r\n  <li>Traffic control plan (only required if you need to block traffic)</li>\r\n  <li>Refer to the Traffic Engineering website(http://www2.oaklandnet.com/Government/o/PWA/o/EC/o/TS/OAK026469).</li>\r\n  <li>Visit the Permit Center</li>\r\n  <li>Once you arrive at the Permit Center’s Information Counter, ask for an Obstruction Permit.</li>\r\n  <li>When your number is called, proceed to the indicated counter.</li>\r\n  <li>Provide the required information</li>\r\n  <li>Pay the permit fee</li>\r\n  <li>The Permit Center accepts cash, checks payable to the City of Oakland and most major credit cards.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"where-to-apply-for-an-obstruction-permit\">Where to Apply for an Obstruction Permit</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr><th>Location</th><th>Hours</th></tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:white\">\r\n\r\nPermit Center\r\n\r\n250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, 2nd Floor\r\n\r\nOakland, CA 94612\r\n\r\n</td><td>\r\n\r\nMondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 8 a.m. to 4 p.m.\r\nWednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4 p.m.*\r\n*last Wednesday of each month from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m.\r\n\r\n</td></tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"cost-of-the-obstruction-permit\">Cost of the Obstruction Permit</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The cost of an Obstruction Permit varies. The cost depends on the period of time for the permit, the number of parking spaces required and the type of parking spaces blocked. \r\nFor more information, please call the Permit Center at (510) 238-3443.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 21:58:04', '2016-01-07 00:52:20', '13e70aaa-fdd0-42d3-bd86-7db44e6a95b1'),
 ('92', '92', 'en_us', 'Apply for a Residential Parking Permit', 'Download the permit applicatio', 'You can apply for a parking permit through the Residential Parking Permit (RPP) program. This permit will allow you park your vehicle in certain neighborhoods in Oakland. You need to register your vehicle to an eligible address to receive the permit.', 'http://www2.oaklandnet.com/Parking/OAK046014', '<p>You can apply for a parking permit through the Residential Parking Permit (RPP) program. This permit will allow you park your vehicle in certain neighborhoods in Oakland. You need to register your vehicle to an eligible address to receive the permit.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"what-you-need-to-know-before-applying\">What You Need to Know Before Applying</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>To see if your address is eligible, go to__<strong>__</strong><strong>__</strong>_____</li>\r\n  <li>Update your address for your vehicle’s registration and driver’s license with the DMV.</li>\r\n  <li>Click here to update your address with the DMV online. (http://dmv.ca.gov/online/onlinesvcs.htm)</li>\r\n  <li>After updating your address, print the confirmation.</li>\r\n  <li>Submit this confirmation with your application.</li>\r\n  <li>Clear all unpaid parking tickets from the City of Oakland.</li>\r\n  <li>For help, call the Parking Citation Assistance Center at (800) 500-6484.</li>\r\n  <li>Click here to pay parking tickets online.</li>\r\n  <li>To pay by phone, call the Parking Citation Assistance Center at (800) 500-6484.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"how-to-apply-for-a-residential-parking-permit\">How to Apply for a Residential Parking Permit</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You need to submit an application, four supporting documents and the correct fee to apply. The address on your application must match the address on each supporting document.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Application Process</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Click here to download the residential parking permit application.(http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/fma/documents/form/oak046014.pdf)</li>\r\n  <li>Complete the application.</li>\r\n  <li>Include four supporting documents.</li>\r\n  <li>Current vehicle registration</li>\r\n  <li>Current California driver’s license</li>\r\n  <li>Utility bill from the last 30 days. Choose one from the list below.</li>\r\n  <li>Gas bill</li>\r\n  <li>Electric bill</li>\r\n  <li>Water bill</li>\r\n  <li>Garbage bill</li>\r\n  <li>Proof of your current address. Choose one from the list below.</li>\r\n  <li>Rental agreement</li>\r\n  <li>Lease</li>\r\n  <li>Mortgage statement</li>\r\n  <li>Property tax bill</li>\r\n  <li>Deed</li>\r\n  <li>Click here to find your permit fee for your address online (<strong>__</strong><strong>__</strong><em>__</em>)</li>\r\n  <li>For more information you can call the Parking Citation Assistance Center at (800) 500-6484.</li>\r\n  <li>Methods of payment</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You can submit your application, four supporting documents and payment in person or mail them to the Parking Citation Assistance Center:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr><th>Location</th><th>Hours</th></tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:white\">\r\nParking Citation Assistance Center\r\n250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300\r\nOakland, CA 94612\r\nPhone: (800) 500-6484\r\n</td><td>\r\nMondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.\r\nWednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.\r\n</td></tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 22:05:30', '2016-01-07 00:52:21', 'a4eb5ab1-fc9f-4149-8e37-24e1581b9399'),
 ('112', '112', 'en_us', 'Renew Your Residential Parking Permit', 'Renew your permit online', '', 'https://pci.etimspayments.com/pbw/include/oakland/rppinput.jsp', '<p>You can renew your permit online if you received a letter that says you are eligible for online renewal.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"in-person-or-by-mail\">In Person or by Mail</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr><th>Location</th><th>Hours</th></tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:white\">\r\nParking Citation Assistance Center\r\n\r\nAttn: Residential Parking Permits\r\n\r\n250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300\r\n\r\nOakland, CA 94612\r\n</td><td>\r\n- Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays, Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.\r\n- Wednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.\r\n</td></tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-18 22:16:30', '2016-01-07 00:52:21', 'e37ed58e-4f3a-4c3a-954e-cac6cb08c864'),
