 ('372', '372', 'en_us', 'Civil Service Board', '', '', '', '<h3 id=\"responsibilities\">Responsibilities</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Enforces the City’s personnel system and Civil Service Rules</li>\r\n  <li>Approve exemption of positions from competitive service</li>\r\n  <li>Approves classification specifications</li>\r\n  <li>Performs other duties described in specific City laws and the Personnel Manual of the Civil Service Board</li>\r\n  <li>Hears appeals on merit system issues.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"membership\">Membership</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>The Mayor appoints the seven members of the Civil Service Board.</li>\r\n  <li>A majority of City Council must confirm each member.</li>\r\n  <li>Each member can serve for a three-year term.</li>\r\n  <li>A member can serve up to two consecutive terms.</li>\r\n  <li>Other staff include the Personnel Director and an attorney from the Office of the City Attorney.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"activities\">Activities</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>The Civil Service Board meets every third Thursday at 5:30 P.M., at One Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Hearing Room 1</li>\r\n  <li>All meetings are open unless a special closed session is scheduled.</li>\r\n  <li>The general public can comment on any agenda item and speak in an open forum.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"more-resources\">More Resources</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Section 901 of the Charter of the City of Oakland (About the Civil Service Board)</li>\r\n  <li>Article IX of the Charter, Personnel Administration (City of Oakland Personnel System)</li>\r\n  <li>Ordinance No. 13120 CMS</li>\r\n  <li>Ordinance No. 11777 CMS</li>\r\n  <li>Personnel Manual of the Civil Service Board</li>\r\n  <li>Brown Act and the City’s Sunshine Ordinance (closed sessions)</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', '[]', NULL, NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-07 00:49:13', '2016-01-07 00:52:24', '66638691-47ae-4ce9-8f79-0efc3d68a075'),
 ('382', '382', 'en_us', 'Employee Assistance Program (EAP)', '', '', '', '<p>The employee assistance program (EAP) provides City of Oakland employees and their families with free resources. These benefits help address personal and work-related problems. City employees and their families may use these services confidentially.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"examples-of-eap-services\">Examples of EAP Services</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>In-person counseling</li>\r\n  <li>Substance abuse treatment</li>\r\n  <li>Free legal advice and referrals</li>\r\n  <li>Financial services</li>\r\n  <li>Services for your family</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Claremont EAP manages the EAP for the City of Oakland. Request services by contacting their counselors.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"how-to-request-eap-services\">How to Request EAP Services</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr><th>\r\nPhone</th><th>Online</th></tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:white\">\r\nClaremont EAP: (800) 834-3773\r\n</td><td>\r\n[Enroll online](http://claremonteap.personaladvantage.com/gateway.jsp?SingleSignIn:refid=10349826.)\r\n</td></tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', '[]', NULL, NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-07 00:50:18', '2016-01-07 00:52:24', '2b7f73d6-13a0-4cf2-bf7f-113ae45560fa'),
 ('392', '392', 'en_us', 'Requesting a Civil Service Board Hearing or Appeal', '', '', '', '<h3 id=\"what-to-know\">What to Know</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a <strong>permanent classified employee</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>You can appeal the following disciplinary actions:</li>\r\n  <li>Suspension</li>\r\n  <li>Fine</li>\r\n  <li>Demotion</li>\r\n  <li>Discharge</li>\r\n  <li>The Personnel Director receives all notices of appeal.</li>\r\n  <li>Submit your notice of appeal within 10 working days of the final notice of discipline.</li>\r\n  <li>Your union has defined rules to file an appeal and request a hearing in a Memorandum of Understanding.</li>\r\n  <li>Click here to find your union’s Memorandum of Understanding (MOUs) http://www2.oaklandnet.com/Government/o/CityAdministration/d/EmployeeRelations/MOUsandCivilServiceRules/index.htm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a <strong>probationary classified employee</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>You can appeal losing your job under certain conditions.</li>\r\n  <li>If you were not evaluated according to the rules of the Personnel Manual.</li>\r\n  <li>If you were not released according to the rules of the Personnel Manual.</li>\r\n  <li>The Personnel Director receives all notices of appeal.</li>\r\n  <li>Submit your notice of appeal within 5 working days of notice of losing your job.</li>\r\n  <li>Your union has defined rules to file an appeal and request a hearing in a Memorandum of Understanding.</li>\r\n  <li>Click here to find your union’s Memorandum of Understanding (MOUs) http://www2.oaklandnet.com/Government/o/CityAdministration/d/EmployeeRelations/MOUsandCivilServiceRules/index.htm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"what-happens-next\">What Happens Next</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>You will receive a response to your notice of appeal within 7 days.</li>\r\n  <li>Timely appeals must be submitted to the Civil Service Board.</li>\r\n  <li>The Board will decide who will hear the appeal.</li>\r\n  <li>Either the Board or an independent Hearing Officer will hear the appeal.</li>\r\n  <li>Hearings are usually closed to the public unless you request a public hearing.</li>\r\n  <li>The Board has the power to make a final decision.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"contact-the-civil-service-board\">Contact the Civil Service Board</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr><th>In Person</th><th>Phone</th><th>Email</th></tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:white\">\r\nHours: Monday through Friday from 8:30 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.\r\n</td><td>\r\nGeneral Information: (510) 238-6467\r\n\r\nAppeals: (510) 238-6467</td>\r\n<td>\r\n[civilservice@oaklandnet.com](mailto://civilservice@oaklandnet.com)\r\n</td> </tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"more-resources\">More Resources</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Ordinances 8979, 11777, the Personnel Manual - Civil Service Board and the Personnel Rules and Procedures of the Port of Oakland (Appellate duties of the Civil Service Board)</li>\r\n  <li>Rule 10 of the Personnel Manual (Permanent Classified Employee Rights for Appeal to the Civil Service Board)</li>\r\n  <li>Rule 6 of the Personnel Manual (Probationary Classified Employee Rights for Appeal to the Civil Service Board)</li>\r\n  <li>Protocol for Hearing Packet Submission http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/hrm/documents/form/oak052475.pdf</li>\r\n  <li>Hearing Request Form http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/hrm/documents/form/oak052473.pdf</li>\r\n  <li>Rule 6 Probationary Period Procedure in Appeals (PDF) http://www.oaklandnet.com/Civil%20Service/Rule6.pdf</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', '[]', NULL, NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-07 00:50:53', '2016-01-07 00:52:24', '1399fddf-f687-497e-b49a-210aa6e6de6c'),
